OSS License Comprehension Study

Read data

library(dplyr)
userdata <- read.csv("OSSStudy6.csv", header=T)
userdata

Eye Fixation data Clustering (MEL + LEL)

df <- scale(select(userdata, matches('melfix|lelfix|switches'), -matches('task'), -matches('melm|lelm')))
colnames(df)
 [1] "melfixcnthierachy" "melfixcntmodel"    "melfixcnttext"     "lelfixcnthierachy" "lelfixcntmodel"   
 [6] "lelfixcnttext"     "melfixdurhierachy" "melfixdurmodel"    "melfixdurtext"     "lelfixdurhierachy"
[11] "lelfixdurmodel"    "lelfixdurtext"     "melswitches"       "lelswitches"      
hc <- hclust(dist(df))
plot(hc)

groups <- cutree(hc,k =3)
groups <- cbind(userdata$ID, groups)
print(g1 <- groups[groups[,2] == 1,1])
[1] 1 3 4 9
print(g2 <- groups[groups[,2] == 2,1])
[1]  2  6  7  8 10
h <- heatmap(df, distfun = dist, hclustfun = hclust, scale="none")

Significant test between groups

boxplot(group1$conf, group2$conf)
t.test(group1$conf, group2$conf)


    Welch Two Sample t-test

data:  group1$conf and group2$conf
t = 0.71842, df = 7.9917, p-value = 0.493
alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
95 percent confidence interval:
 -22.10403  42.10403
sample estimates:
mean of x mean of y 
     87.5      77.5 
wilcox.test(group1$conf, group2$conf)
cannot compute exact p-value with ties

    Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction

data:  group1$conf and group2$conf
W = 15.5, p-value = 0.5762
alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
